25:49.680 --> 26:00.340
roots do go back to science fiction as I read it beginning at an early age. And
as with most people who read science fiction, I also, when I started, read it

26:00.340 --> 26:12.880
backwards as well as forwards. I would pick up old magazines from the early 40s
and the 30s and I'd get books earlier in the century. And I

26:12.880 --> 26:25.440
think I am a product of, in the sense, of all the science fiction traditions
which went to make up the area. I mean, the space opera is there. The hard

26:25.440 --> 26:37.460
science, I feel it there sometimes, and the reaction to it, which came before
the so-called new wave, the sort of sociological science, that creeps into

26:37.460 --> 26:49.420
sometimes. And then the period itself when I began writing the 60s, being what
